    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_2148820114" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2148820114" />
    <a title="Crystal" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/874154-crystal"><img alt="Crystal" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1373116521p2/874154.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2148820114?book_show_action=true">Oct 23, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Crystal" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Crystal" href="/user/show/874154-crystal">Crystal</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2148820114" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10326892291354493437">I highly recommend this book, especially to folks who live in cities and/or are concerned about gentrification. The author tackles all the big issues in this novel set in Brooklyn&apos;s Bed-Stuy neighborhood--police violence, broken windows, demographic changes, education, employment. <br/><br/>The author attempted to tell the story from quite diverse perspectives. This is where I think he went a bit off track. The characters were well drawn, but I found some of their actions and words implausible, especially</span>
  <span id="freeText10326892291354493437" style="display:none">I highly recommend this book, especially to folks who live in cities and/or are concerned about gentrification. The author tackles all the big issues in this novel set in Brooklyn's Bed-Stuy neighborhood--police violence, broken windows, demographic changes, education, employment. <br /><br />The author attempted to tell the story from quite diverse perspectives. This is where I think he went a bit off track. The characters were well drawn, but I found some of their actions and words implausible, especially those of the African American characters. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10326892291354493437" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

